Merged from ticket 22276104  
      Subject: Refund of wrong product delivered  
      Description:  Sir, I Dipanwita Das had placed order of 3 product i.e Melaglow rich, Gorgeous face cleansing gel and maxrich intensive moisturizing lotion of total Rs 1146.53 Order ID 655565757394452480 on 4th December and got delivery on 7th December totally different item which I didn't order. 
 I mailed to pharmacy stating everything what happened to me on 7 th December, after that pick up was initiated. But another problem raised with the courier service. The courier boy is continuously deliberately cancelling my pick up from Tuesday i.e 9th December till date stating that OTP is not provided from my end. 
 If he call me, visit my place then only it is possible to provide OTP, without visiting how is it possible to provide OTP. After getting the message I called the courier boy whose number is 7980838348, he told me that pick up doesn't fall under his area, so he is cancelling my pick up and he has no other option to cancel. From Tuesday I am facing this problem. I mailed you in this matter on 10 th December but my problem still not resolved neither the pick up is initiated nor I got the refund amount. It has been a week I am facing this type of harrasment. Why am I supposed to suffer like this. 
 How can a person trust Pharmacy if they get such poor facility. I knew that Pharmeasy is a trusted online medicine site but I am totally being scammed. 
 Either you make pick up the product and refund the amount or refund the amount without pickup or reorder the 3 items again on my address without any payment. 
 Do resolve my case as earliest as possible or else I have to complain in Consumer Forum. I have being harrassed a lot. I need to get solution on emergency basis . Do look into my matter on priority basis.  
 I have attached with this trial mail the type of delivery box I received, the bill amount, the product I received and the unpick up messages from the courier service.

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear PharmEasy Support Team,

I am writing to bring to your attention an issue with my recent order. I
received the multivitamin and biotin tablets with the seal already opened,
which makes the product unsafe for consumption. I have also recorded a
complete unboxing video clearly showing the damaged and tampered packaging.

I had planned this order according to my travel schedule. The app indicated
that the delivery would arrive the next day, but I received it two days
later, on the day of my travel. After checking the product, I immediately
contacted customer care, and I was informed that I must return the item to
receive a refund.

However, I am currently out of station, and the product is at my home. Due
to this, I am unable to return the item immediately. I want to emphasize
that this delay was not caused by me. The late delivery and the damaged
product are entirely due to mishandling from your end, which has caused
inconvenience and a health concern for me.

Therefore, I kindly request:

1. Immediate refund initiation, considering the product delivered to me is
unsafe and unusable.


2. I will return the product as soon as I return home.


3. Alternatively, if refund is not possible immediately, please deliver a
replacement product to my current location.



I expect prompt assistance in resolving this matter, as the situation has
affected both my travel plans and my health-related needs.

Thank you for your understanding, and I look forward to a quick resolution.

Warm regards,
Sai Tejas
Phone: 6363721169
Email: saitejas9629@gmail.com

helpdesk_ticket.description_html:
Dear PharmEasy Support Team,

I am writing to bring to your attention an issue with my recent order. I received the multivitamin and biotin tablets with the seal already opened, which makes the product unsafe for consumption. I have also recorded a complete unboxing video clearly showing the damaged and tampered packaging.

I had planned this order according to my travel schedule. The app indicated that the delivery would arrive the next day, but I received it two days later, on the day of my travel. After checking the product, I immediately contacted customer care, and I was informed that I must return the item to receive a refund.

However, I am currently out of station, and the product is at my home. Due to this, I am unable to return the item immediately. I want to emphasize that this delay was not caused by me. The late delivery and the damaged product are entirely due to mishandling from your end, which has caused inconvenience and a health concern for me.

Therefore, I kindly request:

1. Immediate refund initiation, considering the product delivered to me is unsafe and unusable.


2. I will return the product as soon as I return home.


3. Alternatively, if refund is not possible immediately, please deliver a replacement product to my current location.



I expect prompt assistance in resolving this matter, as the situation has affected both my travel plans and my health-related needs.

Thank you for your understanding, and I look forward to a quick resolution.

Warm regards,
Sai Tejas
Phone: 6363721169
Email: saitejas9629@gmail.com
